body_html:
OK, looking closer at logs, it looks like compilation failed because of a syntax error. So the wheel was getting built with an incomplete file set, probably left over from previous build.

The error is that one of the files has
size_typ i = 0; which should be size_type i = 0;
😮

Isn't this kind of thing supposed to get caught by continuous tests?

Someone else is trying to fix it in: #8039

body:
OK, looking closer at logs, it looks like compilation failed because of a syntax error. So the wheel was getting built with an incomplete file set, probably left over from previous build. 

The error is that one of the files has
`size_typ i = 0;`  which should be `size_type i = 0;`
😮 

Isn't this kind of thing supposed to get caught by continuous tests?

Someone else is trying to fix it in: https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/8039
